108	/// One-shot kernel-side test of the slice-3.1a memory APIs. Allocates a
109	/// throwaway [`arch::aarch64::addrspace::AddrSpace`], installs four 4 KiB
110	/// mappings at distinct user VAs (each backed by a fresh frame), walks
111	/// every mapping to verify the VA→PA translation matches what we
112	/// installed, then tears the AddrSpace down. Frees go onto the free list,
113	/// so a follow-up alloc returns one of them — that's the final check.
114	///
